article.title: In Photos | Community Garden Grand Opening
article.description: The new community garden is located at University United Methodist Church, on the corner of Sueno and Camino del Sur.
article.content:
On Sunday morning, UC Santa Barbara’s Edible Campus Program, the Isla Vista Community Services District and University United Methodist Church hosted the grand opening of the Edible Garden Project. The new community garden is located at University United Methodist Church, on the corner of Sueno and Camino del Sur. The event included food, live music, crafts and sidewalk chalk art.

related.title: In Photos | AFSCME & UTPE Hold One-Day Strike
related.description: The unions have been negotiating new contracts with the UC since 2017.
related.content:
On Wednesday, two of the University of California’s unions – American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees 3299 and the University Professional and Technical Employees – held a one-day strike. The unions have been negotiating new contracts with the UC since 2017; both parties have yet to come to an agreement.

This was the third strike from union workers that the UC has seen within the past year.

related.description: This year's Associated Students election saw tears of joy and of disappointment. Relive the night below:
related.content:
This year’s Associated Students election saw tears of joy and of disappointment. Relive the night below:

The Isla Vista Party won three of the five Associated Students executive seats. Jose Ochoa / Daily Nexus

related.description: Daily Nexus photographers captured this year's Deltopia celebrations.
related.content:
